Description: When Everyone Competes - You Win!
Headquarters Regions: Greater Miami Area, East Coast, Southern US
Full Description: EverythingTree connects consumers to providers of services through a process they refer to as "broadcast shopping. It essentially works as follows: 1. Consumers broadcast what they are looking for. 2. EverythingTree forwards this broadcast to Service Providers in the area (for free), without providing them with consumer contact information. 3. EverythingTree relays responses from providers back to the consumers. 4. Consumers choose a provider, and then deactivate the broadcast to stop receiving replies. For Service Providers EverythingTree is a free source of new business leads that is easy to configure and highly targeted. **Management:** Dan McCabe is an engineer with a strong entrepreneurial track record.  Dan recently founded and funded Avalon Integration, a systems integrator focused on SAP R/3.  Profitable in Y1, Avalon had revenue of $3mm in Y3. Before that, as CTO, Dan helped to grow Applied Tactical Systems, an enterprise software firm, from $6MM to $10MM in 3 years and a $26MM exit.  **Market Opportunities:** Consumers typically find providers by â€œcalling around."  This is a time consuming and inefficient search strategy.  Service Providers typically generate leads via advertising or purchase them from lead-capture sites.  This is often expensive and ineffective.   We solve the "matching" problem above, at no cost to the provider or consumer. We disrupt the leads-for-sale (ServiceMagic & Redbeacon) models by providing our leads for free. **Target Markets:**  **PROVIDERS:** Other lead capture sites target specific vertical markets (ServiceMagic targets contractors; SitterCity targets babysitters, etc.) Our market includes ALL service businesses (contractors, lawyers, doctors, car services, nannies etc.). Many are already paying for leads through ServiceMagic, etc.  We now have 87 service providers including 3 national franchises. **CONSUMERS** don't pay at EverythingTree.  The potential market is essentially the craigslist user base which is to say, consumers of most any service, anywhere in the US. **Competitors:** There are many in the lead capture space, including: ServiceMagic, RedBeacon, ProspectVista, LendingTree, etc.  But EverythingTree is DISRUPTIVE: we are the only one attempting to monetize this space in this fashion. Our revenue model is similar to craigslist which is free to nearly everyone, nearly everywhere, but still has revenues of more than $100M with only 38 employees. **Competitive Advantage:** It is difficult to compete on a traditional basis with an offering that is free for nearly every user, nearly everywhere, nearly all the time.  Our early experience has shown that the EverythingTree model is intuitively pleasing for both service providers and consumers and while marketing is definitely necessary to get our message out, we are very confident about the sales conversion rate we will achieve.

Description: XignOff is an app that helps capture and archival of electronic signatures.
Headquarters Regions: San Francisco Bay Area, West Coast, Western US
Full Description: Xignoff is the leading electronic signature capture application for mobile devices.  Available on the iPhone App Store and the Android market. XignOff is an application designed to capture signatures using mobile touchscreen devices (iPhone, iPod Touch, iPad or Android). These signatures and their identity are permanently saved (while your account is in good standing) in our cloud together with metadata specific to each signature: time, date and location. The metadata stamped on the captured signature certifies the time, date and place it was captured (providing that the device’s time and date settings are set accurately and its positioning service is enabled) and, at the same time, ensures that the signature is unique and hasn’t been used anywhere else (e.g. copy/paste).

Description: Philly Restart is a non-profit that works to get the homeless men and women of Philadelphia back on their feet.
Headquarters Regions: Greater Philadelphia Area, Great Lakes, Northeastern US
Full Description: I used to walk by homeless men and think, “Why don’t you just get a job?” I would give a beggar a dollar or buy him a slice of pizza, and continue with a pocket full of stereotypes about the poor, drunk, and lazy. One afternoon, I didn't walk by, and I stopped to gently ask that question that bothered me after buying a man a burger. I was shocked at the answer that I heard, "I can't get a job, I don't have an ID."  And then I asked the same question and got the same answer as I shared meals with the homeless across the country. I found that a common theme for many of them was that they did not have proper identification. And you need ID to get ID.  And money to pay for it.  It's a vicious cycle.  A few years later, I heard the same stories on the streets of Philadelphia. Men and women wanted to work, but they couldn't get back on their feet. They needed help. Philly Restart was formed to meet the immediate need of hunger, but focuses on helping men and women to take steps towards full and healthy lives.

Full Description: DryVax is a technology that allows the manufacture of vaccines that have aluminum-containing adjuvants into a dosage form that is not sensitive to freezing, intentionally or unintentionally. This technology will also open markets that lack cold-chain storage and as a result were unreachable for broad vaccine distribution.

Description: Turkish food is pure love on a warm plate and Cafe Turko.
Headquarters Regions: Greater Seattle Area, West Coast, Western US
Full Description: Turkish food is pure love on a warm plate and Cafe Turko genuinely reflects the traditional cuisine and warm hospitality of its native culture. The homemade cooking and exquisite tastes immediately transport you to the Mediterranean in a whirlwind of mystic atmosphere and decor. Enjoy a shopping trip browsing selections representative of the Middle East markets while your table becomes ready. Cafe Turkos pita pocket sandwiches blend the flavors of home with modern convenience. The doner kebab pocket stuffs sliced doner alongside homemade tomato sauce, grilled eggplant, yogurt sauce, salad greens, and feta cheese crumbles. Cafe Turkos grilled eggplant durum marries the flavors of grilled eggplant with a homemade yogurt and tahini sauce, kalamata olives, just a bit of lemon juice, and feta cheese crumbles. Sureyyas Decorated Ekmek comes on a baked flatbread with spicy beef, feta cheese, and selected vegetables. Nowhere else will you find Cafe Turkos selection of specialty Turkish drinks. Delight your senses with Afghani Greens, a secret blend of green tea leaves infused with cardamom pods and served iced. Indulge in one of the most popular summer refreshments of the Ottoman Palace with the Ottoman Rose Sherbet, an aromatic rose sherbet and lemonade punch served with rose petals floating on the surface. The Sage Sultanate tea comes from the coast of the Mediterranean and carries just a hint of lemon juice over ice. Of course Cafe Turko serves traditional Turkish coffee! Cafe Turkos dazzling selection of traditional Turkish dishes will captivate and delight your senses. Savor their aromatic lamb with sweet and sour apricots topped with slivered almonds. Brave the grilled, spiced chicken with eggplant and yogurt sauce steeped in Antep seasonings. The Turkish ravioli is unforgettable, stuffed with beef, garlic, and yogurt and drizzled with tomato sauce and butter. Many of the selections are available with gluten-free or vegan options. Dont be afraid to ask for what you want. Well find a way to make it for you. Cafe Turko will transport you to another place and time with food that is out of this world. Dine in and enjoy the atmosphere of a completely different world!
